If your app is on the Salesforce Platform, you can publish events using an Apex method or with the Flow Builder declarative tool. 
If your app is an external app, you can publish events using Salesforce APIs, including Pub/Sub API and the data APIs, like REST API.

 The EventBus.publish() method returns a Database.SaveResult object, which contains the result of the publishing. If isSuccess() returns true, 
 the publish request is queued in Salesforce and the event message is published asynchronously. If isSuccess() returns false, the event publish 
 operation results in errors, which are returned in the Database.Error object. This method doesn’t throw an exception due to an unsuccessful publish operation.
 
To publish more than one event in the same call, add your events to a list of events, and pass the list to the EventBus.publish() method. The output of this method 
is an array of Database.SaveResult objects: one for each published event. EventBus.publish() can publish some passed-in events, even when other events can’t be published 
due to errors. The EventBus.publish() method doesn’t throw exceptions caused by an unsuccessful publish operation. 

To get confirmation of the final event publishing result, use Apex Publish Callbacks.

