Subscribe:

On the Salesforce Platform, you subscribe to events using Apex triggers, processes, flows, and the empApi Lightning component. In an external app, you subscribe to events using Pub/Sub API.

Platform events support only after insert triggers. 
A trigger processes platform event notifications sequentially in the order they’re received. The order of events is based on the event replay ID. An Apex trigger can receive a batch of events at once.
Asynchronous Trigger Execution ( publish and subscribe both are diffrent transaction.
The batch size in a platform event trigger is 2,000 event messages, which is larger than the Salesforce object trigger batch size of 200.
